name: ENTITY
description: The root node

feature_types.explain: In extension of
Has a part
Is part of
Experienced as
Prototype
Source
Associated with

name: ABSTRACT
description: Something that doesn't exist physically, nor is an event

name: REAL
description: A real object or event.

name: INDIVIDUAL
description: An entity that occurs as a singular or is not compositional.

name: IDEAL
description: An abstract entity that represents a desired state. For example, 'order' in 'law and order'

name: PROPOSITIONAL
description: A statement or an abstract component of speech- such as sentence

name: QUANTITY
description: An entity that can be either measured, is numerical or is related to measurement

name: IRREAL
description: An entity that doesn't exist in the world/imaginary/mythological

name: QUALITY
description: An entity relating to an observed quality such as kindness

name: PHYSICAL
description: A physical object

feature_types.explain: The general shape of an object (mostly geometrical shapes, but exceptions may exist
The size of an object (use vehicles or buildings for comparison (ex: elephant-> big-> truck sized)
The common color of an object
The material property (steel, paper, fibers, biological tissue, etc)
The texture of an object (smooth, rough, etc)
The common odor associated with object
The common taste associated with object
The common location of an object
Strength of the object
The physical state of an object (gas, liquid, solid...)

name: SENTIENT
description: A human type with specific traits and goals.

feature_types.explain: The distinctive trait of a particular sentient. For example, lawyers are commonly quick-thinking, etc
The goal of a sentient. For example, lawyers have the goal to win cases for clients.

name: NATURAL
description: A naturally occuring entity (not created/developed by human)

name: SOCIAL
description: An entity created by humans or arising from society.

feature_types.explain: Either what an object is used for, or what a person/sentient does
The prerequisites or required tools or objects to function
The manner in which a SOCIAL entity is processed/created/comes to be

name: STATIONARY
description: A physical entity that does not move.

name: LIVING
description: A biologically living entity.

feature_types.explain: The source of a living object- example mammals are mainly through 'live births'
Where the living entity is commonly found
What the living entity is composed of/body form
The age of a living entity

name: NONLIVING
description: A non-living entity.

name: STATIONARY
description: Describes things that are normally immobile, attached to the earth and moved only at great effort.

name: NONSTATIONARY
description: Describes things that are able to move or be moved.

name: SELFMOVING
description: Describes things that are normally in motion or designed for motion, in some cases with no apparent initial source.

name: NONSELFMOVING
description: Describes things that are normally immobile but can be moved with slight effort.

name: COLLECTIVE
description: Describes a group of entities as a whole.

name: MASS
description: Even the smallest amount is of the same material nature as the collective term (a drop of water is still water), and whose members are referred to only in terms of measurable units.

name: SET
description: Each member of the set is the same kind as every other member.

name: STRUCTURE

feature_types.example: management,staff
feature_types.explain: describes the roles inside the structure

feature_types.example: managers are in charge of managing staff
feature_types.explain: explains the duty and responsibility of the role

description: Each member is of the same kind type as every other member; members have specified relations with one another.

name: TEMPORAL
description: There is a time aspect to the entity in question.

name: RELATIONAL

feature_types.example: Times Square
feature_types.explain: describes where it occured.

feature_types.example: 2100 hours
feature_types.explain: describes when it happened.

feature_types.explain: describes what allowed an event to happen

feature_types.example: Thus 1600 people perished in the fires
feature_types.explain: describes the consequences of the event

feature_types.example: Subsequently more efforts were channeled into raising awareness for forest fires
feature_types.explain: describes subsequent events following the inital event

description: Verbs are attached here.

name: NONRELATIONAL
description: Temporal nouns (nouns that relate to time i.e, seasons) go here.

name: INSTITUTION
description: An institution is a collective entity that works towards a goal, and is a byproduct/part of society.

name: MAMMAL
description: A mammal is a vertebrate that generally is nourished with milk at young age, has hair on skin and is warm-blooded. For example, humans, bears, tiger.

name: PHYSICAL_QUALITY
description: This refers to abstract concepts in language that serve to convey the PHYSICAL quality of an object (such as it's reliability, effectiveness, etc)

name: IDEAL_GROUP
description: This refers to abstract concepts that denote a collective ideal scenario/setting.

name: COMMUNICATIVE_EVENT
description: Refers to nouns denoting a communicative event between two entities.

name: DOMESTIC_VERTEBRATE
description: A domestic (one that is groomed in presence of sentients) vertebrate (an animal possessing a backbone/spine) such as fish, reptiles, mammals, birds and amphibians.

name: PLANT
description: A plant based entity

name: COGNITIVE_CONCEPTION
description: This refers to concepts that denote abstract cognitive phenomena that can be measured empirically

name: KITCHEN_TOOL
description: A tool found/used in the kitchen or for it's related activities.

name: REGION
description: Refers to a collective region spanning an area.

name: NATURAL_STATE_GROUP
description: Refers to the natural states of the world that are thought of in a collective sense.

name: MANMADESYSTEM
description: A manmade system comprising of multiple entities. It differs from an INSTITUTION since it is not SENTIENT.

name: DOMESTIC_ANIMAL
description: Refers to domestic (brought up in the presence of sentients in a SOCIAL setting) animals

name: HERD
description: A herd refers to a large group of animals, and in this case, observed in a SOCIAL setting.

name: WORK
description: Refers to concepts related to the activity of working in a SOCIAL setting.

name: DOMESTIC_BIRD
description: Refers to a domestic (brought up in the presence of sentients in a SOCIAL setting) bird.

name: EMOTIONAL_STATE
description: Refers to an emotional state.....

name: IDEAL_THING
description: Refers to concepts denoting ideal individual states/setting.

name: COLLECTION
description: A nonliving, nonselfmoving, social collection of objects.

name: NUMERICAL
description: An entity denoting a numerical/mathematical value.

name: SOCIAL_PEOPLE_GROUP
description: A group comprising of social sentients that have a goal.

name: DOCUMENT
description: Refers to physical or virtual documents that have a purpose and other attributes.

name: COMPLEX
description: A social complex/system/structure composing of individual entities.

name: DISCOURSE
description: Involves concepts relating to communication

name: GOAL_ORIENTED_ACTIVITY
description: Refers to social goal oriented activities.

name: FLORA
description: Relating to a group of plant like entities.

name: ACT_OF_GOD
description: Refers to natural nonmental event based nouns.

name: MUTUAL_STATE
description: Refers to concepts denoting a mutual state between two entities- mostly sentients.

name: PEOPLE_EVENT
description: Refers to social events involving people/sentients.

name: ROLE
description: Refers to a specific SOCIAL role

name: MINERAL
description: Refers to naturally occuring minerals.

name: FLEET
description: Refers to a collection of social objects.

name: NATURAL_PLACE
description: Refers to a natural place in this universe

name: PERSON
description: Refers to a human being/person evoking SENTIENT attributes in contrast to the KT Human (which represents more PHYSICAL attributes)

name: MEASURE
description: Refers to entities denoting the units of measurement of other entities.

name: DOMESTIC_PLANT
description: Refers to a domestic (grows in presence of sentients in a social setting) plant based entity.

name: CROP
description: Refers to a domestic (grows in presence of sentients in a social setting) plant based entity.

name: HUMAN
description: Refers to a human being in relation to its PHYSICAL attributes as opposed to the kind type PERSON (which refers to the more SENTIENT attributes)

name: HISTORICAL_EPOCH
description: Refers to a span of time in which certain SOCIAL activities/development took place.

name: PRIMATE
description: Refers to a specific type of mammal relating to monkeys, apes, humans, etc

name: COMPANY
description: A specific INSTITUTION that operates in society and works towards a goal.

name: PART
description: Refers to general physical parts (both NATURAL and SOCIAL)

name: ANIMAL
description: Refers to a general ANIMAL (specializes into various types of ANIMALS).

name: CULTURE
description: A microbial culture, is a method of multiplying microbial organisms by letting them reproduce in predetermined culture medium under controlled laboratory conditions.

name: NATURAL_PROCESS
description: A process existing in or produced by nature (rather than by the intent of human beings).

name: STUFF
description: An unspecified material substance or aggregate of matter.

name: LOWER_ORDER_GROUP
description: Refers to a species of lower lifeforms that do not move on their own such as plants or fungi

name: CHEMICAL
description: Any basic substance that is used in or produced by a reaction involving changes to atoms or molecules.

name: BIRD
description: Any animal which has wings, has a beak, is covered in feathers and lays eggs.

name: BOVINE
description: Any of a subfamily of bovids including oxen, bison and their close relatives.

name: MANMADEPART
description: Refers to components of any man-made machines.

name: VERTEBRATE
description: Any type of animal which possesses a backbone.

name: FLOW_GROUP
description: Refers to the collective form of entities which flow.

name: MANMADEOBJ
description: Describes anything (whole object, not just components) made by man.

name: FISH
description: Fish refer to any animals with gills and fins.

name: NATURALSYSTEM
description: A biological classification based upon morphological and anatomical relationships and affinities considered in the light of phylogeny and embryology.

name: task
description: A usually assigned piece of work often to be finished within a certain period of time.

name: MOVING_OBJECT
description: Any object that moves.

name: FLOW
description: Describes a steady, continuous stream or supply of something.

name: POST_GOAL_EVENT_RESULT
description: Describes the outcome of an event.

name: maintenance
description: Maintenence refers to the process of preserving a condition or situation or the state of being preserved.

name: IRREAL_GROUP
description: An organization that holds an event to which others are invited.

name: PERSONALITY
description: Personality refers to individual differences in characteristic patterns of thinking, feeling and behaving.

name: SOCIAL_PROCESS
description: A process that often involves human effort

name: NATURALPART
description: A part of an individual entity that occurs naturally.

name: BODY
description: A collection of people

name: CULTURE_GROUP
description: Defines a group of biological cultures

name: FAUNA
description: The animals of a particular region, habitat or geological period.

name: EQUIPMENT
description: The set of necessary tools, clothing, etc. for a particular purpose.

name: UBIQUITOUS_ABSTRACT_CONCEPTION
description: Refers to intangible everyday phenomena that cannot be felt using the five senses

name: AIR_VEHICLE
description: Refers to a machine that is able to fly by gaining support form the air.

name: ARTIFACT
description: Refers to any constructs which are made by humans.

feature_types.example: A pencil  performs its function of writing by gripping the pencil shaft, placing the lead on the paper and moving the lead to create words.
feature_types.explain: Describes the performance and implementation of the function of a thing.

feature_types.example: A shirt is constructed by sewing.
feature_types.explain: Details how the entity is constructed

feature_types.example: An airplane is owned by an airline.
feature_types.explain: Describes the owner of the entity.

name: VEHICLE
description: A thing used for transporting people or goods.

feature_types.example: A car moves by burning fuel using its combustion engine, which causes its wheels to turn.
feature_types.explain: Describes the how the vehicle moves.

feature_types.example: A car is driven by 1 driver.
feature_types.explain: Describes the nature of the driver.

feature_types.example: For every 50 passengers on an airplane there is 1 cabin crew allocated.
feature_types.explain: Describes the crew of the vehicle.

feature_types.example: A car usually has space for 4 passengers.
feature_types.explain: Describes the passengers of the vehicle.

name: ACT_OF_GOD_GROUP
description: An instance of uncontrollable natural forces in operation.

name: COGNITIVE_ACTIVITY
description: Describes activity relating to, being, or involving conscious intellectual activity.

name: PROPOSITION
description: A a statement putting forth an idea, suggestion or plan.

feature_types.example: The sentence contains an argument calling for the death penalty to be legalized
feature_types.explain: Describes the things that are held or included in something.

feature_types.example: This argument was put forth by John
feature_types.explain: Describes the person who originated or gave existence to the entity described
Describes anything an entity has.

feature_types.example: He presented his arguments with the goal of legalising euthanasia.
feature_types.explain: Describes the intended outcome.
Functions performed by the entity.

name: transportation
description: Describe the means of moving humans, animals or goods from one location to another.

name: IMAGINARY
description: Describes entities that are not real.

name: FUEL
description: A fuel is any material that can be made to react with other substances so that it releases energy as heat energy or to be used for work.
